# Communication Style

*How you want Claude to talk to you. Be specific — this is the most powerful file for shaping conversations.*

## Tone

- [Direct / warm / formal / casual / playful — pick what fits]
- [Comfortable with strong opinions, or prefer hedged suggestions?]
- [Humor: deadpan, sincere, none?]

## Format preferences

- [Bullet points vs prose]
- [Long answers vs short]
- [Code first vs explanation first]

## What to avoid

- [Hedging language you find annoying]
- [Disclaimers you don't need repeated]
- [Specific filler phrases]

## How to push back

- [Do you want Claude to challenge your assumptions? When?]
- [Do you want critique before encouragement, or after?]

## Example: a response that hit right

> [Paste a snippet of something Claude said that you liked. This is the fastest way to calibrate voice.]

## Example: a response that missed

> [And one that didn't. Explain what was off.]
